result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyler E. Calvi was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC (2nd+ Offense), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

records.addlTxt: 11:49 am case called. Defendant Tyler E. Calvi in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement reached and stated on the record-Amend Count 3 to Misd. Bail Jumping in violation of 946.49(1)(a). Attorney Szilagyi concurs. Preliminary hearing waived. Court questions defendant and accepts waiver of right to preliminary hearing. Court has read the complaint, finds probable cause, and enters an order binding the defendant over for trial. Information filed. Attorney Szilagyi confirms receipt, waives formal reading.   Defendant advised of permissible punishment.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Court accepts motion to Amend Count 3 as stated by ADA Anderson. Plea: No Contest to Count 1 & 3.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in Count 2 and criminal conduct from MI on 5-16-16-Illegal Possession of a Controlled substance and 7/11/16-Unauthorized operation fo a motor vehicle. No statement by defendant. Court sentences the defendant to: SWD and places the defendant on probation for a period of 2 years.  CONDITIONS: AODA and follow through, defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.  Terms of Agent. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Bond on file to be applied. DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.
Plea/sentencing hearing on September 16, 2016 at 11:45 am.

Statement by Attorney Szilagyi regarding non-appearance of defendant-in custody in MI and would be released on September 8th. Statement by Attorney Blader regarding non-appearance. Further discussion between counsel and court regarding settlement. Court adjourns plea/sentencing to afford the defendant the opportunity to appear.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for September 16, 2016 at 11:45 am.
